&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appnovation is a global, full-service digital partner that combines Strategy, Experience &amp;amp; Design, Engineering and Managed Services. We build digital solutions that deliver real impact today and serve as foundations for future growth.&amp;nbsp; Bold ambition. Practical action. Endless possibilities.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&quot;page-3&quot; class=&quot;_kqswh2mm _bfhku67f _18u01wug _2hwx1wug&quot; data-testid=&quot;page-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appnovation is seeking a Senior Lead, IT to lead our IT team, reporting directly to the IT Director. In this role, you will oversee the full spectrum of IT operations—from infrastructure and security to end-user support and SaaS administration—ensuring our technology environment is reliable, secure, and scalable.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a hands-on leader, you will drive strategic IT initiatives, mentor a team of IT professionals, and collaborate cross-functionally with Operations, and Engineering stakeholders. You will be instrumental in shaping Appnovation’s IT roadmap, improving service delivery, and strengthening our security posture across modern cloud based corporate systems and platforms.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appnovation prides itself on having an open environment focused on teamwork and growth, giving you the opportunity to guide your own workload and grow your career.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Own&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership &amp;amp; Strategy&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, mentor, and develop the IT team, including IT associates and security specialists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute the IT strategy and roadmap in alignment with business objectives and the IT Director’s vision&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement across IT processes, workflows, and documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report regularly to the IT Director on team performance, project status, and strategic recommendations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infrastructure &amp;amp; Operations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee global network infrastructure across all office locations, including LAN/WAN, VPN, and wireless connectivity&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage multi-cloud infrastructure, server administration, DNS, DHCP, and backup systems&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead endpoint lifecycle management for Mac laptops and other devices, from deployment through disposal&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer and optimize the corporate collaboration environment, including user provisioning and security policies&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own IT asset inventory, procurement, and vendor relationships&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SaaS &amp;amp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identity&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the SaaS application portfolio, including licensing compliance and spend optimization&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead identity and access management strategy, including SSO, MFA, and role-based access controls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate, onboard, and integrate new SaaS solutions to improve productivity and operational efficiency&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Security &amp;amp; Compliance&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strengthen the organization’s security posture by implementing and maintaining information security controls&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
